<!-- ################# Donation Process Start Here #######################--->
<section id="process" class="donation-care">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row session-title">
            <h2 style="font-family:Arial">Donation Process</h2>
            <h6 style="font-family:Arial">The donation process from the time you arrive in a center and until the time you leave</h6>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 vd">
                <div class="bkjiu">
                    <img src="assets/images/gallery/g1.jpg" alt="">
                    <h4 style="font-family:Arial"><b>1 - </b>Registration</h4>
                    <p>
                        First you need to register in the website as a donor.
                        In this stage you shall be asked for your health status and age, as well as information for any diseases which you may know from previous examinations.
                    </p>                   
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 vd">
                <div class="bkjiu">
                    <img src="assets/images/gallery/g2.jpg" alt="">
                    <h4 style="font-family:Arial"><b>2 - </b>Apply for donation</h4>
                    <p>
                        You have to apply for donation with respect to request from hospital or directly donate to a hospital blood bank. 
                        In this stage you shall be able to select donor availability status - i.e, when you shall be ready for donation procedure.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 vd">
                <div class="bkjiu">
                    <img src="assets/images/gallery/g3.jpg" alt="">
                    <h4 style="font-family:Arial"><b>3 - </b>Donation</h4>
                    <p>Blood donation - the amount of donated blood is between 405 and 450 ml. The bag in which it is collected has a special solution with a volume of 63 ml. 
                    It maintains the life of blood cells and thanks to it the blood and blood components retain their healing properties for up to 36 days.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 vd">
                <div class="bkjiu">
                    <img src="assets/images/gallery/g4.jpg" alt="">
                    <h4 style="font-family:Arial"><b>4 - </b>Save Life</h4>
                    <p>You are providing the medical institutions with the necessary blood and blood components in order to perform life-saving operations and emergency medical interventions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>





